                \b Amazon's Strategy Explained\b0\par
                Amazon's strategy is built on three pillars: low prices, vast selection, and convenience. The company continually invests in its fulfillment and logistics network to make shopping as easy as possible for customers. \par
                This is a very important point.{\atnauthor (Amazon Analyst)}{\atnid a1}{\atntime 1710926715}\b\v This comment explains the importance of this sentence.\v0}\par
                \par
                Another key part of the strategy is the flywheel effect, where a positive customer experience drives more traffic, which attracts more sellers, and so on. This creates a virtuous cycle of growth.
